1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 {This move is considered the best move, and is also the 
most played one! The reason is that it opens lines and diagonals for White's 
pieces faster.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 {Attacking the e4-pawn.} 5. Nc3 g6 {And here we 
have our lovely system: The Dragon! It is one of the most played defences 
against 1. e4. Almost every Sicilian player began their Sicilian career playing 
the Dragon, because of the ease of Black's piece development and the clear plans 
available to him!} 6. Bc4 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. Re1 {So as to play Nd5, provoking 
... Nxd5, which will be met by exd5, activating the e1-Rook and putting pressure 
on the e7-pawn.} Nc6 {Attacking the d4-Knight and putting yet more heat on it.} 
9. h3 Bd7 {Creating space for the Rook to come to c8.} 10. Bg5 {Adding indirect 
pressure to the e7-pawn.} Nxd4 {Luring the White Queen to the same diagonal as 
the Bishop on g7.} 11. Qxd4 h6 12. Bd2 Ng4 {[%cal Gg7d4,Bg4e5][%csl Rd4] 
Attacking the Queen and heading towards an attack on the c4-Bishop.} 13. Qd3 Ne5 
{[%csl Rd3,Rc4] Fork!} 14. Qe2 Bxh3 $1 {Followed by:} 15. gxh3 Qc8 $17 {[%cal 
Gc8c4,Bc8h3,Ge5f3][%csl Rc4,Rh3,Rg1] Attacking both the c4-Bishop and the 
h3-pawn, which Black will follow with ...Nf3+.} *

