[Comment "short-and-sweet-the-sicilian-dragon/course/31190, variation/5714612"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 {This move is considered the best move, and is also the 
most played one! The reason is that it opens lines and diagonals for White's 
pieces faster.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 {Attacking the e4-pawn.} 5. Nc3 g6 {And here we 
have our lovely system: The Dragon! It is one of the most played defences 
against 1. e4. Almost every Sicilian player began their Sicilian career playing 
the Dragon, because of the ease of Black's piece development and the clear plans 
available to him!} 6. f4 {Threatening to advance with e5 immediately, so Black 
needs to be careful.} Nbd7 {Played to prevent e5.} 7. Nf3 {[%cal Be4e5] Renewing 
the threat of e5.} Qc7 {[%cal Gc7e5] Adding more defenders to the e5-square.} 8. 
Bd3 Bg7 {White has no threat, so Black can calmly complete his development.} 9. 
O-O O-O 10. Qe1 a6 {[%cal Bb7b5,Bb5b4,Bc8b7,Gf6e4,Gb7e4][%csl Re4] Preparing to 
play ... b5 followed by ... Bb7 and then ... b4, which should win the pawn on 
e4.} *

