1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 {This move is considered the best move, and is also the 
most played one! The reason is that it opens lines and diagonals for White's 
pieces faster.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 {Attacking the e4-pawn.} 5. Nc3 g6 {And here we 
have our lovely system: The Dragon! It is one of the most played defences 
against 1. e4. Almost every Sicilian player began their Sicilian career playing 
the Dragon, because of the ease of Black's piece development and the clear plans 
available to him!} 6. Bb5+ {Played with the idea of developing as quickly and as 
simply as possible, however this doesn't really create any serious problems for 
Black.} Bd7 {The simplest way.} (6... Nbd7 {is possible as well.}) 7. Bg5 
{Putting pressure on the f6-Knight and indirectly on the e7-pawn as well.} Bg7 
8. Qe2 {Preparing Queenside castling.} a6 {Played to simplify the position.} 9. 
Bxd7+ Nbxd7 10. h4 {Begins an attack on the Kingside, so White is effectively 
always going to castle on the Queenside now.} Rc8 {Preparing counter-play on the 
Queenside.} 11. Rh3 {White supports the c3 Knight, defending against the 
thematic ... Rxc3 sacrifice.} h6 {Kicking the Bishop away.} 12. Be3 Rxc3 $1 13. 
bxc3 Nxe4 {[%cal Ge4c3][%csl Rc3]} 14. Bxh6 Nxc3 $15 {[%cal Gc3e2,Bh8h6][%csl 
Rh6]} *

