1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 {This move is considered the best move, and is also the 
most played one! The reason is that it opens lines and diagonals for White's 
pieces faster.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 {Attacking the e4-pawn.} 5. Nc3 g6 {And here we 
have our lovely system: The Dragon! It is one of the most played defences 
against 1. e4. Almost every Sicilian player began their Sicilian career playing 
the Dragon, because of the ease of Black's piece development and the clear plans 
available to him!} 6. h3 {Preparing for an early g4 push.} Bg7 7. g4 {Opening 
the diagonal for the light-squared Bishop, and preparing a possible assault on 
the Kingside.} Nc6 {Threatening ...Nxd4 to lure the Queen to the same diagonal 
as the g7-Bishop.} 8. Nde2 {The same idea as the g3-system.} O-O 9. Bg2 Rb8 
{[%cal Bb7b5] Preparing for ...b5 with expansion on the Queenside, and at the 
same time Black moved his rook away from the h1-a8 diagonal, where it would be 
on the same diagonal as the g2-Bishop.} 10. O-O b5 11. a3 Nd7 {[%cal 
Bd7c5,Gg7b2,Ba7a5,Bb5b4] Opening the diagonal for the g7-Bishop and getting 
ready to play ...Nc5.} 12. Be3 a5 {[%cal Bb5b4] In order to play ... b4, which 
is going to fix the c2-pawn.} 13. Ra2 {[%cal Ga2b2] To keep the b2-pawn 
protected.} b4 14. axb4 axb4 15. Nd5 e6 {Moving the Knight away from the 
centre.} 16. Ndf4 b3 17. cxb3 Nc5 $15 {[%cal Gb8b3,Gc5b3,Gg7b2][%csl Rb3,Rb2] 
Attacking the b3-pawn. Black enjoys the superior pawn structure. Not only b3, 
but b2 is also seriously weak and isolated.} *

