1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 {This move is considered the best move, and is also the 
most played one! The reason is that it opens lines and diagonals for White's 
pieces faster.} cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 {Attacking the e4-pawn.} 5. Nc3 g6 {And here we 
have our lovely system: The Dragon! It is one of the most played defences 
against 1. e4. Almost every Sicilian player began their Sicilian career playing 
the Dragon, because of the ease of Black's piece development and the clear plans 
available to him!} 6. Bg5 Bg7 7. f4 {The drawback of this move is that it 
weakens the g1-a7 diagonal.} Nc6 {Attacking the d4-Knight.} 8. Bb5 {Pinning the 
Knight and threatening ...Nxc6.} O-O $5 {Sacrificing a pawn in order to gain 
better development!} 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. Bxc6 Bg4 {Attacking the Queen.} 11. Qd3 
Rb8 {[%cal Gb8b2][%csl Rb2] Attacking the b2-pawn.} 12. Ba4 Rxb2 13. Bb3 {[%csl 
Rb2] Attempting to trap the Rook.} Nxe4 $1 {[%cal Gg7a1][%csl Ra1] Exploiting 
the fact that the Rook on a1 is undefended!} 14. Nxe4 Rxb3 {[%cal Bg7a1,Gb3d3] 
Now both the Rook on a1 and White's Queen are attacked.} 15. axb3 Bxa1 $17 
{Black is a pawn up for no compensation.} *

